  "difficulty": "L3",
  "snapshot": "os",
  "instruction": "A local launch brief is available at ~/Desktop/deploy_launch_brief.html. Open it in Chrome with the file:// URL and keep it open while you work. Then use ~/Desktop/deploy_config.json as the source of truth for all concrete values: create the log directory from logDir, write ~/Desktop/env_summary.txt with the project and author lines from the config, create the service directory from serviceDir with a README.md whose first line is '# <project>' and whose second line is 'Owner: <author>', create a .env.example file in that service directory containing the LOG_DIR and SERVICE_NAME values from the config, and apply the VS Code User Settings from the config by setting editor.tabSize, editor.rulers, and each entry from excludeDirs in files.exclude.",
  "source": [
    "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/",
    "https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/getstarted/settings",
    "现实场景构造来源：服务上线前常见的“依据 launch brief 和 deploy_config 生成目录、README、.env.example 与排除规则”部署包整理流程"
